@flexiarg measurement/ghost-as-typed-sorry
@title Null Conflates Many Absences — Type Your Ghosts
@sigils [👻/⊢]
@keywords ghost, null, absent measurement, typed hole, sorry, proposal-mode, not-yet, excluded confound, absence discipline
@audience anyone whose records contain absent values that downstream readers must interpret
@tone procedural
@style pattern

! conclusion: An absent measurement is not one thing. "Null" conflates absences that license OPPOSITE inferences — not-measured-yet, deliberately-excluded-confound, proposal-mode (would-be-measured-under-enactment), measurement-impossible-here. Type every ghost: the absence carries a kind, and the kind is part of the record's meaning.

  + context: Real measurement loops are full of holes — values that do
    not exist yet, cannot exist, or exist only counterfactually. The
    default representation for all of them is the same null.

  + IF:
      A record has fields that are legitimately absent (the loop ran in
      preview mode; a confound was excluded; the reading comes later).

  + HOWEVER:
      All absences render identically, so a reader (human, model, or
      gate) cannot distinguish "we chose not to act, so the outcome is
      counterfactual" from "we haven't measured yet" from "this can
      never be measured" — and every inference drawn from the record
      silently assumes one of these.

  + THEN:
      Give the ghost a type from a small fixed vocabulary (e.g.
      :proposal-mode / :not-yet / :excluded-confound /
      :absent-unless-supplied), stored in the record itself. Enforce
      absence discipline at the schema (a typed-hole :kind field), so
      an untyped null is a validation error, not a shrug.

  + BECAUSE:
      A typed absence is a typed hole — a sorry with an interface that
      says what would discharge it — and typed holes are enumerable,
      rankable, and dispatchable, while nulls are folklore. Distinct
      absences license distinct inferences; the type is what makes the
      difference checkable. (This is [[proof-search/typed-hole-as-frontier]]
      applied to measurement; kin:
      [[measurement/error-needs-structure-to-teach]].)

  + canonical-instance:
      M-first-flights (futon3c): the flight-record ghost table —
      velocity present with its typed target, counterfactual and
      begin-state as ghosts — with the absent-unless-supplied whitelist
      already enforcing ghost discipline at the projector, and
      sorrys.edn schema v2's :kind as the typed-hole vocabulary the
      ghosts adopt. The prediction organ "holds the typed ghost" for
      Phase B by design.
